              long<ns0:lb /> hair, which falls down her back behind, and<ns0:lb /> from each shoulder before,
              to her breasts.<ns0:lb /> Her right hand is placed under her left<ns0:lb /> breast, and with the
              other she supports her<ns0:lb /> infant son. She has bracelets on her arms;<ns0:lb /> and the
              lower part of her body from the wast<ns0:lb /> to her ancles is cloathed with a linen
              gar=<ns0:lb /> ment like that of <ns0:add rend="underline">Osiris</ns0:add>. The head of Orus<ns0:lb />
              is shaved, except on large lock of hair,<ns0:lb /> which remaining on the right side rests
              on<ns0:lb /> that shoulder: He has also a lote on his<ns0:lb /> forehead and his body is naked.

                inches, on a wooden ped <ns0:hi rend="sup">l</ns0:hi>.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>

              <ns0:add rend="pencil">E H</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">9</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>Harpocrates sitting in the character of a <ns0:add rend="underline">Pantheon</ns0:add><ns0:lb />
              with the attributes of several deities. His head is<ns0:lb /> adorned with a Crown of Ivy
              over which is a<ns0:lb /> Lote, and a crest on the front. A bulla hangs<ns0:lb /> at his breast,
              which with the left of the body<ns0:lb /> is naked. The forefinger of his right hand is
              placed<ns0:lb /> on his chin, and a <ns0:add rend="underline">Cornu Copia</ns0:add> with a
              Serpent<ns0:lb /> twinning round it, rests on his left arm, which<ns0:lb /> is supported by a
                <ns0:add rend="underline">Sphinx</ns0:add> , and an owl sits<ns0:lb /> perching on his right
              knee. Hight 4 1/4<ns0:lb /> inches. on a wooden pedestal.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">[A S M] </ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">E H</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">

              <ns0:add rend="ink">XXXIV. 15</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">-99.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>The <ns0:measure type="sizeWeight">small</ns0:measure> seall of the parl <ns0:hi rend="sup">t</ns0:hi>. made by <ns0:persName>
                <ns0:metamark function="carets">T.</ns0:metamark> Simons </ns0:persName><ns0:add rend="underline">1rst year</ns0:add><ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">of <ns0:add rend="del">clity</ns0:add> freedom by Gods blessing</ns0:add>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">

              <ns0:add rend="red">✓</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
            <ns0:p><ns0:add rend="underline">Magnum sigillum Rei pub. Angliæ Scotiæ & Hiberniæ</ns0:add>
              &c. Olivers <ns0:metamark function="carets">Lead.</ns0:metamark> arms <ns0:add rend="del">on

            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="ink">XXXIV. 19</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">12.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">101.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="red">✓</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
            <ns0:p><ns0:add rend="underline">sigillum Commune Col. Reg. Medicorum Landin.</ns0:add> made in
              1737. Red <ns0:material>wax</ns0:material> in a box.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">19.</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="ink">XXXIV. 39</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">-102.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p><ns0:add rend="underline">Henricus Fil. Richards.</ns0:add> A head w<ns0:hi rend="sup">t</ns0:hi>.
              this legend ab <ns0:hi rend="sup">t</ns0:hi>. it it is in a flint sett in<ns0:lb /> a pretty
              clumsey <ns0:measure>piece</ns0:measure> of <ns0:note type="colour">silver</ns0:note> & was found
              at last spring at Fordwic <ns0:gap reason="illegible" /> in <ns0:placeName ref="#Kent">Kent</ns0:placeName> by <ns0:persName>M<ns0:hi rend="sup">r</ns0:hi>. Rickersey</ns0:persName> as he
              was dressing his sparagis bed. <ns0:persName>D<ns0:hi rend="sup">r</ns0:hi>. Pack</ns0:persName><ns0:lb />
              Red <ns0:material>wax</ns0:material> in a box.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">19.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">103.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>An Impression on Wax (or Rye-Paste) of <ns0:persName> Henry y<ns0:hi rend="sup">e</ns0:hi> 8<ns0:hi rend="sup">th's</ns0:hi></ns0:persName><ns0:lb /> Broad Seal: having on one Side the King
              sitting on<ns0:lb /> his Throne; <ns0:add rend="del">with</ns0:add> on the other, the King on Horseback:<ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">19.</ns0:add> the Legend on both Sides is the same: viz: <ns0:add rend="underline">Henricus</ns0:add><ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">Octavus Dei Gra: Angliæ et Franciæ Rex, Fidei</ns0:add>
              <ns0:gap reason="illegible" />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">Defensor, et Dominus Hiberniæ.</ns0:add></ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="red">✓</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="ink">XXXIV 6</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">104</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="red">✓</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>Another <ns0:measure type="sizeWeight">smaller</ns0:measure> in Wax of the same <ns0:persName>
                King</ns0:persName>, having<ns0:lb /> on one side a different figure of Henry & seated on
              his<ns0:lb /> Throne, the Legend imperfect, but seems to be: Sigillum<ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">19.</ns0:add> Augmentacionum corone Henrici Octavi Regis<ns0:lb /> Angliæ et
              Francie.<ns0:lb /> On the Reverse, the King armed on horseback, with<ns0:lb /> his Crown, &
              y <ns0:hi rend="sup">e</ns0:hi> El<ns0:gap reason="illegible" /> pher H R. the Legend so imperfect,
              that<ns0:lb /> I can read only <ns0:add rend="underline">Capitis Ecclesie</ns0:add>.<ns0:lb /> It seems
              to be the seal of the Augmentation office.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="ink">XXXIV. 7</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">105.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="red">✓</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>An Impression in Wax of <ns0:persName> Queen Elizabeth's</ns0:persName> Great<ns0:lb /> Seal,
              bearing on one side a standing Figure of y <ns0:hi rend="sup">e</ns0:hi> Queen<ns0:lb /> in her
              Regalia (and a Ruff); on the Reverse her Figure<ns0:lb /> on horse back: with this Legend
              on Both Sides:<ns0:lb /> Elizabeth Dei gra: Anglie, Francie et Hibernie<ns0:lb /> Regina Fidei
              Defensor, cap. <ns0:add rend="underline">ECCL</ns0:add> ?</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">19.</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="red">XXXIV. 10</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">106.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="red">✓</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>Another of D <ns0:hi rend="sup">o</ns0:hi> ( <ns0:measure type="sizeWeight">smaller</ns0:measure> and
              older) on one Side the Queen<ns0:lb /> sitting on her Throne, on y <ns0:hi rend="sup">e</ns0:hi>
              other her figure on horseback,<ns0:lb /> (without a Ruff.) the Legend on both sides the
              same seem<ns0:lb /> to be: Elizabetha Dei gracia. Anglie, Francie & Hibernie<ns0:lb />
              Regina, Fidei Defensor.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">19.</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="ink">XXXIV. 11</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">107.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="red">✓</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>Another of <ns0:persName> King James I</ns0:persName>. (large) having the King<ns0:lb /> seated on
              his Throne, on one Side; and on the other,<ns0:lb /> on horseback arm'd, with the
              Legend: Jacobus D. G &c.<ns0:lb /> as above.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="ink">XXXIV. 13 <ns0:add rend="del">12</ns0:add></ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">19.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">108.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="red">✓</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>An old Impression of a Seal on Wax, being the figure of<ns0:lb /> an armed Man on
              Horseback, with this Legend in Letters, <ns0:placeName>paris</ns0:placeName><ns0:lb /> Roman,
                <ns0:measure>part</ns0:measure> Gothick. <ns0:add rend="underline">Sigillum Thornæ de Sco
                (Sancto?) Walerico</ns0:add><ns0:lb /> and on the back his arms <ns0:gap reason="illegible" /> in
              a tri <ns0:measure type="shape">angular</ns0:measure> field; w <ns0:hi rend="sup">th</ns0:hi> y <ns0:hi rend="sup">e</ns0:hi> Legend abridged.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="red">XXXIV 30</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">19.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">109</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="red">✓</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>An <ns0:measure>impression</ns0:measure> on <ns0:note type="colour">red</ns0:note> Wax of an oval
              Seal of some<ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">19.</ns0:add> Archbishop of <ns0:placeName ref="#Canterbury">Canterbury</ns0:placeName>, with this Legend: S. (Sigillum?)<ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">Willi: co <ns0:add rend="red">urtney</ns0:add> dei gra: Cantuarien:
                archiepi.</ns0:add><ns0:lb /> (N.B. the back of this is <ns0:note type="colour">green</ns0:note>
              wax.)</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="red">XXXIV. 66</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">110.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="red">✓</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
            <ns0:p><ns0:add rend="underline">Sigillum S<ns0:figure rend="symbol" /> ti Albani Anglorum P<ns0:figure rend="symbol" /> tomartiris</ns0:add>. A large<ns0:lb /> Oval seal cut in Bone, having on it
              y <ns0:hi rend="sup">e</ns0:hi> figure of S <ns0:hi rend="sup">t</ns0:hi>. Alban,<ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">18.</ns0:add> with a Cross in his hand: [defaced by the Destroyers<ns0:lb />
              of the Monastery.]</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="red">XXXV. 41.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">111.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="red">✓</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>A pretty <ns0:measure type="sizeWeight">large</ns0:measure> oval Seal cut in Brass, w <ns0:hi rend="sup">th</ns0:hi> a handle & Loop<ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="pencil"><ns0:figure rend="symbol" /></ns0:add> The Inscription round the field is:
                <ns0:add rend="underline">S. Fraternitatis</ns0:add><ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">ospitalis Sti Thomæ mart in Roma.</ns0:add></ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">18.</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="red">XXXV. 40.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">112.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="red">✓</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>A <ns0:measure type="sizeWeight">smaller</ns0:measure> oval Seal <ns0:metamark function="carets">cut</ns0:metamark> in Brass containing the history of<ns0:lb /> the Annunciation, viz: the
                <ns0:metamark function="carets">arch</ns0:metamark> Angel Gabriel, the Virgin Mary<ns0:lb />
              & the Holy Ghost descending on her, and at bottom a Monk<ns0:lb /> in a praying
              posture: with this Inscription round the field:<ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">Ave Maria gracia plena Dñs tecum</ns0:add>.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">18.</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="red">XXXV. 48.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">113.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="red">✓</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>A <ns0:measure type="sizeWeight">smaller</ns0:measure> oval Seal cut in Brass bearing a
              Monk's head,<ns0:lb /> w <ns0:hi rend="sup">th</ns0:hi> a hand over it pointing down to it:
              The Motto seems to be:<ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">S. Decanati de S. SVB <ns0:metamark function="carets"><ns0:add rend="underline">E</ns0:add></ns0:metamark> YRI.</ns0:add><ns0:lb /> (Mem: this was 515. of
              Antiquities.)</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">18.</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">
                <ns0:figure rend="symbol" />
              </ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="red">XXXV. 44.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">114.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="red">✓</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">✓ 199 c <ns0:add rend="del">18</ns0:add></ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>Another <ns0:measure type="sizeWeight">smaller</ns0:measure> cut in Brass, bearing a
                <ns0:persName>Hand</ns0:persName> pointing out,<ns0:lb /> with this Inscription: <ns0:add rend="underline">Dat Deus omnebonũ</ns0:add>.<ns0:lb /> [This was 516 of antiquities.]</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="red">XXXV. 50.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">115.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="red">✓</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>A round Seal cut in Brass <ns0:metamark function="carets">w <ns0:hi rend="sup">th</ns0:hi> a
                handle</ns0:metamark> having two heads facing each other,<ns0:lb /> with a Bird over them:
              and a Motto round the field, w <ns0:hi rend="sup">ch</ns0:hi> seems<ns0:lb /> to be: <ns0:add rend="underline">Love me and <ns0:add rend="del">e</ns0:add>
                <ns0:add rend="red">give</ns0:add>
                <ns0:add rend="del">them</ns0:add></ns0:add>. (This was 517 of Antiquities.)</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">18.</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="red">XXXV. 51.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">116.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="red">✓</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>A round brass Seal, w <ns0:hi rend="sup">th</ns0:hi> a loop or Stem on y <ns0:hi rend="sup">e</ns0:hi> back. The Engraving<ns0:lb /> is a Lamb, w <ns0:hi rend="sup">th</ns0:hi> a Flag or
              Ensigns on its back; and this Motto:<ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">Ecce Agnus Dei.</ns0:add></ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">18.</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="red">XXXV. 47.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">117.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="red">✓</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>Another D <ns0:hi rend="sup">o</ns0:hi>. but larger, w <ns0:hi rend="sup">th</ns0:hi> a Wolf <ns0:note type="texture">engraved</ns0:note> on a Shield, and this Motto<ns0:lb /> +: <ns0:add rend="underline">SIGILLV∞: GVILLAM LVP</ns0:add> *.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">18.</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="red">XXXV. 34.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">118.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="red">✓</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>A substantial round Silver Seal, with four holes<ns0:lb /> in the handle or Stem, <ns0:note type="texture">engraved</ns0:note> with a Coat of<ns0:lb /> Arms, & this Inscription:
                <ns0:add rend="underline">Sigillu: Tthel: ap: Bledyn.</ns0:add></ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">18.</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="red">XXXV. 27.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">119.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="red">✓</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>A round Brass Seal (with a handle or Spike fit for<ns0:lb /> setting in a haft) <ns0:gap reason="illegible" />having a <ns0:add rend="del">Griffin</ns0:add> Chineera cut in it, and
              an<ns0:lb /> Inscription, w <ns0:hi rend="sup">ch</ns0:hi> Seems to be: <ns0:add rend="underline">Lucas</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
            <ns0:gap reason="illegible" />
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">18.</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="red">XXXV. 46.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">120.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="red">✓</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>An Impression struck in Brass (in y <ns0:hi rend="sup">e</ns0:hi> manner of a<ns0:lb /> Medal) of
              the Seal of the Quinze Vingts at Paris,<ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">with this <ns0:add rend="del">Inscription:</ns0:add></ns0:add><ns0:lb /> having
              on one Side a King of <ns0:placeName ref="#France">France</ns0:placeName> in his Regalia<ns0:lb />
              standing, & stretching out his right hand to three figures<ns0:lb /> kneeling in a
              suppliant posture; at his left hand <ns0:add rend="underline">a House</ns0:add> :<ns0:lb /> with
              this Inscription: <ns0:add rend="underline">Sigil<ns0:figure rend="symbol" /> Domus Pauperum
                Cecorum</ns0:add><ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">Parisius</ns0:add>. on the Reverse a Kings Bust, w <ns0:hi rend="sup">th</ns0:hi> this Inscript <ns0:hi rend="sup">n</ns0:hi> :<ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">S. Domus Cecorum Paris</ns0:add>.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">18.</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="red">XXXV. 39.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">121.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A Copper Seal Ring with a head cut in it w <ns0:hi rend="sup">ch</ns0:hi> out a Motto. H. to
              left.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">AWF.</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">18.</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add hand="later">A.W.F. 1854.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">122.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">✓ 18.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>A brass Seal Ring, with a Lyon rampant cut in it. no Motto.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">A W F</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add hand="later">A.W.F. 1854.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">123.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A Silver Stone Ring, set w <ns0:hi rend="sup">th</ns0:hi> an Onyx of three Layers, plain.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">18.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">124.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A Silver Seal Ring <ns0:metamark function="carets">wreath'd outside</ns0:metamark> ,
              with this Inscription &c <ns0:note type="texture">engraved</ns0:note> on it.<ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline"><ns0:figure rend="pen" /></ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">A.W.F</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">✓ 18</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add hand="later">A.W.F. 1854.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">125.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>An antique Head (an? once of y <ns0:hi rend="sup">e</ns0:hi> Roman Emperor's)<ns0:lb /> cut
              in an oct <ns0:measure type="shape">angular</ns0:measure>
              <ns0:measure>piece</ns0:measure> of Steel, and set in a round<ns0:lb />
              <ns0:measure>piece</ns0:measure> of Ivory, w <ns0:hi rend="sup">th</ns0:hi> a Screw on it behind.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">✓ 18.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">127.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>The Adcration of our Savior by the shepherds in y <ns0:hi rend="sup">e</ns0:hi><ns0:lb /> Stable:
              a rais'd <ns0:measure>impression</ns0:measure> , Lead, round, pretty Large.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">CH<ns0:gap reason="illegible" /> 2.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">128.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="red">✓</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>The Arms of a Cardinal, cut in Brass (round & bigger than<ns0:lb /> a Crown piece)
              with this Inscription round it:<ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">Vinc: Agn: Suar</ns0:add> : et: <ns0:add rend="underline">Mant: ac: S:
                R: T: Princ.</ns0:add></ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">2.</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="ink">XXXIV 61</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">129.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="red">✓</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>The Arms of Sueden? <ns0:note type="texture">engraved</ns0:note> in Copper (round)<ns0:lb /> with
              this Inscription:<ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">Ericus XIII. D. G. Suec. Gott Wandal. Rex.</ns0:add></ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">2</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="red">XXXIV. 46.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">130.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>The Consecration of a <ns0:add rend="underline">Bishop</ns0:add> (or Abbot) by three<ns0:lb />
              Bishops in their Episcopalia) with a Monk behind y <ns0:hi rend="sup">m</ns0:hi><ns0:lb /> holding
              a Crozier. [Boldly raised on a <ns0:measure type="sizeWeight">large</ns0:measure> oval<ns0:lb />
              <ns0:measure>piece</ns0:measure> of Lead.]</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">3.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">131.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A <ns0:add rend="underline">Shepherdess</ns0:add> in a mourning posture, supporting<ns0:lb /> the
              (naked) dead <ns0:measure>body</ns0:measure> of a <ns0:persName>Shepherd</ns0:persName> i <ns0:add rend="del">on</ns0:add> n her Lap, w <ns0:hi rend="sup">th</ns0:hi><ns0:lb /> a Landskip &c
                <ns0:metamark function="carets">Lead</ns0:metamark> Large, round, raised work.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">CH<ns0:gap reason="illegible" /> 3</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">132.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A Hermit sitting on a Rock with a Jug in his right<ns0:lb /> hand, his left Stretch'd
              out towards two Ravens<ns0:lb /> flying down to <ns0:add rend="del">wards</ns0:add> him, w <ns0:hi rend="sup">th</ns0:hi> a Loaf in the Bill<ns0:lb /> of each: &c. The Story of S <ns0:hi rend="sup">t</ns0:hi>. Anthony the Anachoret ?<ns0:lb /> Lead, the same size, work &c w
                <ns0:hi rend="sup">th</ns0:hi> the preceeding: w <ns0:hi rend="sup">th</ns0:hi> a Loop to it.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">3.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">133.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A <ns0:add rend="underline">Negro's</ns0:add> head or Bust, boldly raised, on an oval<ns0:lb />
              <ns0:measure>piece</ns0:measure> of Lead, bronzed.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">3.</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">A W F</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">M R</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">134.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>Ten figures standing together, the principal is a <ns0:add rend="underline">Woman</ns0:add><ns0:lb /> holding a Child in her left hand, and Standing before an<ns0:lb /> Altar,
              with the front of a Church above them, with an<ns0:lb /> Angel flying to one of the
              Cornishes.<ns0:lb /> Lead, oval, raised work.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">3.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">135.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>Two <ns0:add rend="underline">Angels</ns0:add> standing, & joining hands, with the
              Sun<ns0:lb /> over them. Cut or struck into an oct <ns0:measure type="shape">angular</ns0:measure>
              <ns0:measure>piece</ns0:measure> of<ns0:lb /> Lead.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">CH<ns0:gap reason="illegible" /> 3.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">136.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>The Bust of a <ns0:add rend="underline">Lady</ns0:add> , well raised on Lead: <ns0:metamark function="carets">or Tin</ns0:metamark> large<ns0:lb /> with a Loop at top.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">CH<ns0:gap reason="illegible" /> 3.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">137.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p><ns0:add rend="underline">Cupid</ns0:add> sleeping on a Sopha or Couch, on which are<ns0:lb />
              hung his Bow and Quiver of Arrows: a Tree on his<ns0:lb /> left hand. Basso relievo on a
              round <ns0:measure>piece</ns0:measure> of Lead.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">CH<ns0:gap reason="illegible" /> 3.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">138.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>S <ns0:hi rend="sup">t</ns0:hi>. George killing the Dragon with a Sword.<ns0:lb /> In Lead, oval,
              rais'd work.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil"><ns0:figure rend="symbol" /> 4.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">139.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p><ns0:add rend="underline">The same</ns0:add> , with a Spear. Tin or Lead.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">AWF 4.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">140.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>Two figures standing, <ns0:add rend="underline">Mars & Venus</ns0:add> ? Cast Iron,
              small, oval.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">4.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">141.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A <ns0:add rend="underline">head</ns0:add> (of a Roman <ns0:add rend="underline">Emperor</ns0:add> ?)
              wreath'd w <ns0:hi rend="sup">ch</ns0:hi> Laurel.<ns0:lb /> Struck in <ns0:gap reason="illegible" /> Cast Iron.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">4.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">143.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p><ns0:add rend="underline">Horn soit qui mal y pense</ns0:add> : in the Garter round the<ns0:lb />
              Coat of Arms of the <ns0:persName>Duke <ns0:add rend="pencil">of
              Monmouth</ns0:add></ns0:persName><ns0:lb /> In Lead, small.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">✓ 4.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">142.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>An <ns0:measure>impression</ns0:measure> of a <ns0:add rend="underline">Head</ns0:add> with <ns0:measure type="sizeWeight">short</ns0:measure> Hair, in cast<ns0:lb /> Iron. oval. in cis.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">CH<ns0:gap reason="illegible" /> 4.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">144. <ns0:add rend="del">143</ns0:add></ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>Five Figures standing round a <ns0:add rend="underline">Pillar</ns0:add> set on a
              Pedestal<ns0:lb /> w <ns0:hi rend="sup">th</ns0:hi>. an equestrian Statue ony <ns0:hi rend="sup">e</ns0:hi>
              top. an <ns0:add rend="underline">Columna Antonina?</ns0:add><ns0:lb /> Relief on cast Iron.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">4.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">145.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="red">✓</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>Two Coats of Arms with a Thistle above them, and<ns0:lb /> an Inscription round: <ns0:add rend="underline">S De Maccullagh</ns0:add> ?<ns0:lb /> Tin. small.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">4</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="ink">XXXIV. 76</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">146.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A Figure of <ns0:add rend="underline">Hercules</ns0:add> , w <ns0:hi rend="sup">th</ns0:hi> his Club
              on his Shoulder,<ns0:lb /> and Lion's <ns0:add rend="del">Skill</ns0:add> Skin in his right
              hand. A raised<ns0:lb /> Impression on cast Iron. oval. little.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">CH<ns0:gap reason="illegible" />.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">147.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>The <ns0:add rend="underline">head</ns0:add> of a <ns0:add rend="underline">Lady,</ns0:add> with her
              hair tied up, boldly<ns0:lb /> rais'd on Tin oval.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">CH<ns0:gap reason="illegible" /> 4.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">148.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>The <ns0:add rend="underline">head</ns0:add> of a Danish <ns0:add rend="underline">Admiral</ns0:add>
              w <ns0:hi rend="sup">th</ns0:hi> the Elephant on his breast:<ns0:lb /> raised in Lead.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">4.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">149.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>The Bust of a Roman <ns0:add rend="underline">Emp <ns0:hi rend="sup">r</ns0:hi></ns0:add>
              wreath'd<ns0:lb /> with Laurel, boldly raised work, on Tin. Oval pretty<ns0:lb /> large,
              with a Loop.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">CH<ns0:gap reason="illegible" /> 5.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">150.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>Seven Figures, the principal a <ns0:add rend="underline">woman sitting</ns0:add> , w <ns0:hi rend="sup">th</ns0:hi> a Base<ns0:lb />
              <ns0:abbr>Vid</ns0:abbr> behind her: Mercury's Caduceus &c. a <ns0:measure type="sizeWeight">large</ns0:measure> round<ns0:lb />
              <ns0:measure>piece</ns0:measure>
              <ns0:metamark function="carets">of</ns0:metamark> raised work in Tin.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">CH<ns0:gap reason="illegible" /> 5.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">151.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p><ns0:add rend="del">The</ns0:add> A pretty <ns0:measure type="sizeWeight">large</ns0:measure> round
              Impression (or Medal) raised<ns0:lb /> on Lead, with a Loop at top: having on one Side<ns0:lb />
              The Creation & fall of Man, viz adam & Eve eating<ns0:lb /> the Apple, w <ns0:hi rend="sup">th</ns0:hi> various Animals &c: & this Inscript <ns0:hi rend="sup">n</ns0:hi> :<ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">Et sicut in adam<ns0:gap reason="illegible" /> omnes moriuntur, ita
                et in</ns0:add><ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">Christum onmes vivificabuntur, unusquisque in</ns0:add><ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">ordine suo</ns0:add>.<ns0:lb /> On the other Side,Christ ony <ns0:hi rend="sup">e</ns0:hi> Cross, with the<ns0:lb /> two thieves crucifying likewise, w <ns0:hi rend="sup">th</ns0:hi> this Motto:<ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">Ut Moses erexit Serpentē, ita Chr<ns0:figure rend="symbol" /> in
                Cruce</ns0:add><ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">exaltatus et resuscitatus caput Serpētis cōleruit</ns0:add><ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">ut salvaret Credētes</ns0:add>. ( <ns0:add rend="underline">Creation
                & Redemption</ns0:add>.)</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">5.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">152.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>An Impression on Sulphur tinged <ns0:note type="colour">brown</ns0:note> (round)<ns0:lb /> being
              two standing figures joining hands before<ns0:lb /> an Altar; above is a hand with a
              thunderbolt<ns0:lb /> appearing throw<ns0:gap reason="illegible" /> Clouds: and this Inscription:<ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">Fulmine Sancit</ns0:add>. (a <ns0:add rend="underline">Marriage
                Ceremony</ns0:add>.)</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">5.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">153.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A <ns0:add rend="underline">Woman</ns0:add> 's head with her hair plaited, & tied
              behind:<ns0:lb /> a raised Impression <ns0:add rend="del">raised</ns0:add> on Lead (Oval.)</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">5.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">154.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>Two <ns0:add rend="underline">heads</ns0:add> , the foremost that of a Man
              wreath'd,<ns0:lb /> the hindmost that of a woman, y <ns0:hi rend="sup">e</ns0:hi> hair
              plaited.<ns0:lb /> A roman <ns0:add rend="underline">Emperor</ns0:add> & Empress? raised on
              Lead (oval.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">5.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">155.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A Queen (an <ns0:add rend="underline">Dido</ns0:add> ?) stabbing her Self, in her<ns0:lb />
              Palace; with a Pile of wood behind her. A raised<ns0:lb /> Impression on Lead, round.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">5.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">156.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A <ns0:add rend="underline">Landskip</ns0:add> containing <ns0:add rend="underline">Diana</ns0:add>
              winding a hunting<ns0:lb /> horn, w <ns0:hi rend="sup">th</ns0:hi> a Javelyn in her right hand, and
              Dogs<ns0:lb /> about her: above her head appear <ns0:add rend="del">s</ns0:add> the Moon and<ns0:lb />
              Stars: &c. with this Motto: <ns0:add rend="underline">Par ubique Potestas</ns0:add>.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">5.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">157.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="red">✓</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
            <ns0:p><ns0:add rend="underline">The Seale of the Parliament of the Common</ns0:add><ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">Wealth of England</ns0:add>. an <ns0:measure>impression</ns0:measure> in
              Sulphur.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="ink">XXXIV. 17</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">5.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">158.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>The <ns0:add rend="underline">Apostles</ns0:add> with the Virgin Mary sitting iny <ns0:hi rend="sup">e</ns0:hi> midst of y <ns0:hi rend="sup">m</ns0:hi>.<ns0:lb /> & y <ns0:hi rend="sup">e</ns0:hi> H. Ghost inform of a Dove appearing above them. Lead</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">5.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">159.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A Bust in Profile of <ns0:persName>
                <ns0:add rend="underline">Henry</ns0:add> 8</ns0:persName>. taken off in <ns0:note type="colour">red</ns0:note> wax:<ns0:lb /> Small.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">9.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">160.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>An <ns0:measure>impression</ns0:measure> in <ns0:note type="colour">red</ns0:note>
              <ns0:material>wax</ns0:material> of <ns0:persName> Oliver</ns0:persName>
              <ns0:add rend="underline">Cromwell's</ns0:add> head<ns0:lb /> from <ns0:persName> M<ns0:hi rend="sup">r</ns0:hi>. Ranby</ns0:persName>'s Seal cut by Claus?</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">10.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">161.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p><ns0:persName> S<ns0:hi rend="sup">r</ns0:hi>. Isaac <ns0:add rend="underline">Newton's</ns0:add></ns0:persName> head <ns0:metamark function="carets">in wax</ns0:metamark>
              from a Cornelian of the<ns0:lb /> Earl of abercorne, cut by Claus la three quarter
              face.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">10.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">162.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>D <ns0:hi rend="sup">o</ns0:hi>. smaller, profile, by D <ns0:hi rend="sup">o</ns0:hi>. for D <ns0:hi rend="sup">o</ns0:hi>. &c. as above.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">10.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">163.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>D <ns0:hi rend="sup">o</ns0:hi>. from a Seal of <ns0:persName> Martin Folkes</ns0:persName> Esq <ns0:hi rend="sup">re</ns0:hi>.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">10.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">164.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>D <ns0:hi rend="sup">o</ns0:hi>. from another of <ns0:persName>M<ns0:hi rend="sup">r</ns0:hi>.
                Bevan</ns0:persName>.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">10.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">165.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>An <ns0:measure>impression</ns0:measure> in Sulphur of an antique <ns0:add rend="underline">Head</ns0:add> , w <ns0:hi rend="sup">th</ns0:hi><ns0:lb />
              <ns0:measure>part</ns0:measure> of an Inscription. viz: <ns0:add rend="underline">KOPAΣ</ns0:add>.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">10.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">166.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>a <ns0:add rend="underline">Bishop's</ns0:add> Coat of arms in wax.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">10.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">167.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>an <ns0:measure>impression</ns0:measure> in <ns0:material>wax</ns0:material> of antiquarian
              Society's Seal.<ns0:lb /> a lighted Lamp w <ns0:hi rend="sup">th</ns0:hi> a label underneath w
                <ns0:hi rend="sup">th</ns0:hi> this motto<ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">non extinguctur.</ns0:add> 1717. and round the Border:<ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">Soc. antiqua. Lond.</ns0:add></ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">10.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">168.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="red">✓</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>The seal of the University of <ns0:add rend="underline">Gottingen</ns0:add>
              <ns0:metamark function="carets">founded</ns0:metamark> establish'd<ns0:lb /> by K. <ns0:persName>
                George II</ns0:persName>. a <ns0:hi rend="sup">o</ns0:hi>. 1737. with this Inscription:<ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">Sigillum Universitatis Regiæ Georgiæ Augustæ</ns0:add>.<ns0:lb />
              impress'd in <ns0:add rend="del">Red</ns0:add> wax.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="ink">XXXIV 37</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">10.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">169.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p><ns0:add rend="underline">Honi Soit qui maly ponse</ns0:add> : in a Garter round the Coat
              of<ns0:lb /> Arms of an English Duke.<ns0:lb /> An <ns0:measure>impression</ns0:measure> in Clay.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">11.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">170.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="red">✓</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
            <ns0:p><ns0:add rend="underline">Sigil. Minerarior. et Metall. Cusor. in anglia Dō. Ter-</ns0:add>.<ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">Hiberniaq. an <ns0:hi rend="sup">o</ns0:hi>. Eliz. Regina</ns0:add>. round a
              Coat of Arms<ns0:lb /> impress'd in Clay.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="red">XXXV. 54.</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">11.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">171.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>The Arms of <ns0:measure type="sizeWeight">great</ns0:measure> Britain &c, with a Lyon
              &c a Griphon for<ns0:lb /> Supporters, and at bottom this Motto. <ns0:add rend="underline">Pupill: adjut</ns0:add>. G whole.<ns0:lb /> encompass'd by this Inscription: <ns0:add rend="underline">Jacobus Dei gratiâ Magnæ</ns0:add><ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">Britanniæ Franciæ et Hiberniæ Rex, fidei defensor</ns0:add>.<ns0:lb />
              Stampt on Leather.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">11.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">172.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p><ns0:add rend="underline">Bacchanalians</ns0:add> , <ns0:add rend="del">two o</ns0:add> viz fiv <ns0:add rend="del">y</ns0:add> e figures, one of w <ns0:hi rend="sup">ch</ns0:hi>. is sleeping<ns0:lb /> with
              a sheep by him, another lying cross a Hogshead: &c.<ns0:lb /> A raised
                <ns0:measure>impression</ns0:measure> on Lead, square, w <ns0:hi rend="sup">th</ns0:hi> y <ns0:hi rend="sup">e</ns0:hi> angles cut off.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">A W F</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">11.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">173.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>The Bust of a <ns0:add rend="underline">Lady</ns0:add> , with a book in her right hand:
              her<ns0:lb /> breast button'd. a raised <ns0:measure>impression</ns0:measure> on Lead.
              round.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">11.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">174.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>Three figures near a Gate or front of a Palace, viz: a<ns0:lb /> King pointing with his
              Scepter to a man at work with<ns0:lb /> a Mallet and Chizle, and another bringing a Load to
              him.<ns0:lb /> with this Inscription round it: <ns0:add rend="underline">Diligite Justiciam
                qui</ns0:add><ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">judicatis lerram</ns0:add>. Relief on Lead, round.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">11.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">175.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A Fleet of <ns0:add rend="underline">Ships</ns0:add> , with an Admiral (<ns0:persName><ns0:add rend="underline">James</ns0:add> Duke of<ns0:lb /> York</ns0:persName>.) standing in a
              commanding posture. at bottom is<ns0:lb /> this Motto: <ns0:add rend="underline">Pro talibus
                ausis</ns0:add>. Plumb. excis. rotund.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">11.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">176.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A City, with a harbour & fleet of ships before it, with<ns0:lb /> this Motto above it:
                <ns0:add rend="underline">Neapolis Malvasiæ</ns0:add> : & at bottom.<ns0:lb /> "Ultra
              sesqui seculum sub jugo Ture. inexpugnab. hubita<ns0:lb /> "TD Virtuti Venetæ cedit,
              et ad prisca redit obsequia<ns0:lb /> "auspic. Ser. <ns0:persName>D. <ns0:add rend="underline">Morosini</ns0:add></ns0:persName> fortitudine. Exe. Corneri Cap. G.<ns0:lb /> "D. 12.
              Aug. 1690." Lead. round.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">11.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">177.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>Two figures sitting in a Cave, viz: a man embracing a<ns0:lb /> woman. a raised Impression
              on Lead, square. ( <ns0:add rend="underline">Aneas</ns0:add> & <ns0:add rend="underline">Dido?</ns0:add> )</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">11.</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">AWF</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">178.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A <ns0:add rend="del">n</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="underline">Altar piece</ns0:add> , or <ns0:measure>part</ns0:measure> of a Church, with
              the figures of<ns0:lb /> two Bishops standing at y <ns0:hi rend="sup">e</ns0:hi> sides, cut or
              stamp'd into Lead,<ns0:lb /> with this Inscription: <ns0:add rend="underline">Prima sedes,
                fidei regula, Ecclesiæ</ns0:add><ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">fundamentum.</ns0:add> (The <ns0:measure>whole</ns0:measure> is

            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">210.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A Sensual <ns0:add rend="underline">Woman</ns0:add> sitting, tempted by
                <ns0:measure>several</ns0:measure> Sins<ns0:lb /> in grotesque figures of Monks &c: <ns0:add rend="del">the</ns0:add> one of which is<ns0:lb /> looking out of the trunk of a Tree. Lead.
              square. large.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">14</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">CH<ns0:gap reason="illegible" />.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">211.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A <ns0:add rend="underline">Landskip</ns0:add> , in w <ns0:hi rend="sup">ch</ns0:hi> is a <ns0:add rend="underline">Woman drawing</ns0:add> Water<ns0:lb /> out of a Well, another giving drink
              in a Pitcher<ns0:lb /> to a man &c. The Story of <ns0:add rend="underline">Rebecca</ns0:add>
              ?<ns0:lb /> Lead, round, large.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">14.</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">AWF</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">212.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>The ascension of our <ns0:add rend="underline">Saviour</ns0:add>. Lead. oval, small.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">14.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">213.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A <ns0:add rend="underline">Ploughman</ns0:add> sitting melancholy on a broken<ns0:lb /> Plough.
              Lead, round, small.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">14.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">214.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>Two naked Figures (Justice & Peace) recumbent and<ns0:lb /> embracing, w <ns0:hi rend="sup">th</ns0:hi>
              <ns0:measure>several</ns0:measure> other ornaments, over w <ns0:hi rend="sup">ch</ns0:hi> this<ns0:lb />
              Motto: <ns0:add rend="underline">Justisia et Pax</ns0:add>. and round the border:<ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">Justitia et Pax osculataæ sunt, misericordia et veritas<ns0:lb />
                obviaverunt Sibi</ns0:add>. Lead, round, very large, well raised.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">15.</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">A.W.F.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">215.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A naked <ns0:add rend="underline">Boys</ns0:add> , standing, and holding a Spear: with<ns0:lb /> a
              Serpent at his feet. Brass, <ns0:metamark function="carets">oblong</ns0:metamark> square, well
              raised.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">15.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">216.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A naked <ns0:add rend="underline">Boy</ns0:add> riding on a Seahorse <ns0:metamark function="carets">in <ns0:gap reason="illegible" /> sea</ns0:metamark> , w <ns0:hi rend="sup">ch</ns0:hi> a vessel<ns0:lb /> pouring out water &c. Copper, <ns0:measure type="shape">oblong</ns0:measure> Square, well raised.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">15.</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">AWF</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">217.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A Groupe of figures, chiefly naked <ns0:add rend="underline">boys</ns0:add> playing, the<ns0:lb />
              fig. in y <ns0:hi rend="sup">e</ns0:hi> middle holding a <ns0:measure type="sizeWeight">large</ns0:measure> handled Cup.<ns0:lb /> Lead. round. large.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">15.</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">
                <ns0:figure rend="symbol" />
              </ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">218.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A <ns0:add rend="underline">Landskip</ns0:add> with figures pursuing <ns0:add rend="underline">rural Diversions</ns0:add> ,<ns0:lb /> as Fishing, Hawking, Fowling &c. Lead. round.
              pretty<ns0:lb /> large.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">15.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">219.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="red">✓</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>A <ns0:add rend="underline">Bishop sitting</ns0:add> , w <ns0:hi rend="sup">th</ns0:hi> Keys in the
              right, & a book in y <ns0:hi rend="sup">e</ns0:hi>. left<ns0:lb /> hand. Cut in Box, Basso
              relievo. <ns0:measure type="shape">Round</ns0:measure> , w <ns0:hi rend="sup">th</ns0:hi> four
              handles<ns0:lb /> or Loops.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">✓</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">16.</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="red">XXXV. 45.</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">MS. Dep <ns0:hi rend="sup">t</ns0:hi></ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">220.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>The Busto of <ns0:persName> K. <ns0:add rend="underline">Henry VIII</ns0:add></ns0:persName>. relief
              on Silver gilt, round.<ns0:lb /> It seems to have been the Cover of a Box.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">16.</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">✓ CH</ns0:add>
              <ns0:gap reason="illegible" />
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">221.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>Another of <ns0:add rend="underline">D <ns0:hi rend="sup">o</ns0:hi></ns0:add>. smaller, an
                <ns0:measure>impression</ns0:measure> i <ns0:add rend="del">o</ns0:add> n wax, on a board.<ns0:lb /> an?
              already enter'd N <ns0:add rend="del">o</ns0:add>. 59?</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">16.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">222.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A last of the <ns0:add rend="underline">preceding</ns0:add> in Chalk.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">✓</ns0:add>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">16.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">223.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A <ns0:add rend="underline">hunting piece</ns0:add> done in a <ns0:measure type="shape">circular</ns0:measure> manner, the middle<ns0:lb /> vacant. Lead, emboss'd, round.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">CH</ns0:add>
              <ns0:gap reason="illegible" />
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">16.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">224.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>Six <ns0:add rend="underline">heads</ns0:add> , three & three, an
                <ns0:measure>impression</ns0:measure> in Chalk. oval.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">16.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">225.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A fleet of <ns0:add rend="underline">Ships</ns0:add> before a City, with naval Ornaments<ns0:lb />
              round the Border. an <ns0:measure>impression</ns0:measure> in <ns0:note type="colour">brown</ns0:note>
              Clay.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">16.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">226.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>Another <ns0:measure type="sizeWeight">smaller</ns0:measure>
              <ns0:add rend="underline">D <ns0:hi rend="sup">o</ns0:hi></ns0:add>. with this Inscription:<ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">Service done against six Ships, July. 31 & aug:1. 16 <ns0:add rend="del">7</ns0:add> 50.</ns0:add></ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">16.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">227.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A King in his regalia, holding a prince in one hand,<ns0:lb /> the other hand on an altar:
              with <ns0:measure>several</ns0:measure> figures standing<ns0:lb /> on the other side of y <ns0:hi rend="sup">e</ns0:hi> altar, the principal of which has his<ns0:lb /> hand on it. (a Treaty
              of Peace w <ns0:hi rend="sup">th</ns0:hi> the Suiss Cantons.) with<ns0:lb /> this Inscription round
              the border:<ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">Nulla dies sub me natoque hæc fædera rumpet.</ns0:add><ns0:lb /> &
              this at bottom: <ns0:add rend="underline">Fædere Helvetico instaurato.</ns0:add><ns0:lb /> An
                <ns0:measure>impression</ns0:measure> on Chalk. round.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">16</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">228.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A naked Boy ( <ns0:add rend="underline">Cupid</ns0:add> ) shooting an ar
                <ns0:measure>row</ns0:measure> out of a Bow.<ns0:lb /> Lead, an <ns0:measure type="shape">oblong</ns0:measure> Square.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">16.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">229.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A Bust, the <ns0:add rend="underline">head</ns0:add> wreath'd, in the antique
              manner.<ns0:lb /> Lead, well raised, oval, small.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">16</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">230.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>The Judgment of <ns0:add rend="underline">Paris?</ns0:add> viz: a naked figure of a man<ns0:lb />
              sitting, and reaching an apple to one of three female figures,<ns0:lb /> who has a Child
              standing by her, and Mercury behind y <ns0:hi rend="sup">e</ns0:hi> man.<ns0:lb /> Lead, well
              raised, small, transverse, oval.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">16</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">231.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>a Company sitting at a Table drinking, the Landlady<ns0:lb /> Standing in an undecent
              posture, telling the Score, with<ns0:lb /> these words above her: <ns0:add rend="underline">Macht selbst die zechg</ns0:add>.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">17.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">232.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A man sitting in a Chair, putting on his Stocking, with his<ns0:lb /> privy parts in
              Sight, a Cat leaping at them, and a Girl<ns0:lb /> behind a Curtain, with this Inscription:<ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">Cauda vah! dependet, cave, Catus prendet</ns0:add>.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">17.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">233.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A shepherd & <ns0:add rend="underline">shepherdess</ns0:add> embracing, near a Tree,
              with<ns0:lb /> this Motto: <ns0:add rend="underline">Pascua amoris, oscula oris</ns0:add>.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">17.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">234.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A <ns0:add rend="underline">Woman</ns0:add> sitting on a Bed, Cupid shooting an Arrow<ns0:lb /> at
              her, a Doctor feeling her Pulse w <ns0:hi rend="sup">th</ns0:hi> one hand, and<ns0:lb /> in the
              other holding an Urinal, at which he looks: w <ns0:hi rend="sup">th</ns0:hi><ns0:lb /> this Motto:
                <ns0:add rend="underline">Vulva doles, Urina docet</ns0:add>.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">17.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">236.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A Gentleman riding from a Country Wench, who holds<ns0:lb /> the Reins, w <ns0:hi rend="sup">th</ns0:hi> this Motto: <ns0:add rend="underline">Amasia! cur ingemescit</ns0:add> ?<ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">quia nesat dum venter crescit</ns0:add>.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">17.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">237.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A <ns0:add rend="underline">Woman</ns0:add> naked, recumbent, a youth, a Dog &
              monkey<ns0:lb /> near her, w <ns0:hi rend="sup">th</ns0:hi> this motto: <ns0:add rend="underline">Vah
                Telotypia! Canis cum simia</ns0:add>.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">17.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">238.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p><ns0:add rend="underline">Bethsheba</ns0:add> entering the Bath, King <ns0:add rend="underline">David</ns0:add> on the<ns0:lb /> battlements of his Palace playing on the Harp, with<ns0:lb />
              this Motto: <ns0:add rend="underline">Sic videre, facit dolere</ns0:add>.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">17.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">240.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A naked <ns0:add rend="underline">woman</ns0:add> recumbent, Cupid standing near her,<ns0:lb />
              and an old man prostrate before her, with this Motto:<ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">Ah quam vills amor senilis</ns0:add>.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">17.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">241.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p><ns0:add rend="underline">Diana</ns0:add> ? bathing, w <ns0:hi rend="sup">th</ns0:hi> her nymphs
              round her, and <ns0:add rend="underline">Action</ns0:add> ?<ns0:lb /> in a Huntsman's Dress,
              having Stag's horns on his head, looking<ns0:lb /> on: with this Motto: <ns0:add rend="underline">Fac lateas et tutus eris</ns0:add>.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">17.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">242.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A Woman holding a Fruit in her right hand, Cupid.<ns0:lb /> standing by, offering her a
              Dish of fruit, with this Motto:<ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">Virginibus prodest, cui pondus inest</ns0:add>.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">17.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">243.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p><ns0:add rend="underline">Fortune</ns0:add> flying from off a winged Globe, w <ns0:hi rend="sup">ch</ns0:hi> two Men<ns0:lb /> endeavouring to detain her by pulling two Cords
              pass'd<ns0:lb /> round her Waist, & this Motto: <ns0:add rend="underline">Ah Fortuna
                bona! me condona</ns0:add>.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">17.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">244.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p><ns0:add rend="underline">Cupid</ns0:add> pointing an Ar <ns0:measure>row</ns0:measure> on a grinding
              Stone, an old<ns0:lb /> man setting by him with a <ns0:measure type="shape">blunt</ns0:measure> ar
                <ns0:measure>row</ns0:measure> in his hand, and<ns0:lb /> this Motto: <ns0:add rend="underline">Venite heus! hebetes, Jiwenes et Senes</ns0:add>.</ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">17.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">245.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A <ns0:add rend="underline">drunken Conversation</ns0:add> , with this Motto:<ns0:lb />
              <ns0:add rend="underline">Implendo lagenam, evacuo crumenam.</ns0:add></ns0:p>
            <ns0:p>
              <ns0:add rend="pencil">17.</ns0:add>
            </ns0:p>
          </ns0:div3>

<ns0:div3 xmlns:ns0="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:ns1="http://www.enlightenmentarchitectures.org">
            <ns1:catnum place="margin" type="primary">246.</ns1:catnum>
            <ns0:p>A <ns0:add rend="underline">gaming Company</ns0:add> , with this Motto:<ns0:lb />
